%S A090073 18,60,1932,43890,62478570,3827339670
%N A090073 a(n) = least number m such that m-1, m+1 are twin primes, m=a*b and there are 2^n - 1 choices for (S, D) where S=a+b, D=a-b (a>b>1) and with both S and D primes.
%C A090073 Note that (m-1)^2+S^2=(m+1)^2+D^2.
%C A090073 If k is the number of distinct prime factors of m, then the maximum number of (S, D) values both primes is 2^(k-1)-1. 18, 60 and 1932 are the only terms of the sequence with all (S, D) values both primes. If we consider 1 to be prime (and pi(1)=0), then the first 3 terms are 6, 30, 462
%e A090073 m=18,(m-1,m+1)=(17,19),{(S,D)}={(11,7)}
%e A090073 m=60,(m-1,m+1)=(59,61),{(S,D)}={(23,17),(19,11),(17,7)}
%e A090073 m=1932 7 (S,D) prime values
%e A090073 m=43890 15 (S,D) prime values....
